# Unit 02

## 1. Overview

This artefact presents the peer feedback i recieved on my Unit 1 discussion and my reflection on how this feedback contributed to my learning.
The purpose of this task was to engage with peer review as part of collaborative learning, allowing me to evaluate the strengths of my work and identify areas for improvement.

Through this process, I was able to gain a deeper understanding of how my analysis could be strengthened, particularly in relation to accountability, transparency and the application of risk management concepts.

## 2. Description of Feedback

The feedback i recieved highlighted several strengths in my original discussion. In particular, the reviewer noted that my work was well structured, clearly written and demonstrated strong critical engagement with the topic. My use of academic sources was also recognized as effective especially in supporting my arguments around algorithmic bias and opacity.

The reviewer agreed with my position that technological systems are not neutral and acknowledged that my argument was well supported by relevant literature. This confirmed that my initial analysis was on the right track.

However, the feedback also provided constructive suggestion for improvement. One key recommendation was to expand my discussion of explainability of algorithmic systems. This included considering the difference between simply making systems transparent and ensuring that they are genuinely understandable and accountable. 

Additionally, the reviewer suggested that i could strengthen my argument by incorporating perspective on external auditing. This would help address limitations associated with internal controls and provide a more robust approach to accountability.

The feedback also encouraged me to further develop my discussion of procedural fairness, particularly in relation to how individuals can challenge decisions made by automated systems.

## 3. Application of Learning Outcomes

INDENTIFICATION AND ANALYSIS OF SECURITY RISKS
The feedback helped to deepen my understanding of the risks associated with algorithmic systems. It showed me that identifying risks is not enough, ut the must also be critically analysed.

INFORMATION GATHERING AND SYNTHESIS
The suggestion to include additional academic perspectives highlighted the importance of using a wider range of sources to support arguments. This has encouraged me to strengthen my research and improve how i integrate different viewpoints.

SELECTION OF METHODOLOGIES AND TECHNIQUES
The introduction of external auditing as a recommendation expanded my awareness of practical techniques that can be used to mitigate risks. This helped me understand how theoretical concepts can be applied in real world contexts.

ETHICAL, LEGAL AND PROFESSIONAL ONSIDERATIONS
The feedback reinforced the importance of fairness, accountability and transparency in system design. It strengthened my understanding of ethical responsibilities when working with data-driven tech.

