## 5. Reflection

Although i did not formally respond to the feedback at the time, reflecting on it has provided valuable insights into how my work could be improved. The feedback made me aware of the importance of going beyond identifying risks to critically analysing how they can be addressed through practical and accountable mechanisms. 

In particular, the distinction between transparency and true accountability was akey learning point. I now recognize that simply making systems visible is insufficient without ensuring that they are understandable and open to challenge.

Thi has influenced my approach to subsequent work in the module, where i have aimed to provide deeper analysis and stronger justification of my recommendations.
